        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 16 at 9:29PM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>At 929 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Charlotte, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Charlotte...           Eaton Rapids...        Potterville...
Aurelius...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
